trans-unit.source: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API
trans-unit.target: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API

trans-unit.source: This topic provides descriptions of the properties of the <system>Contact</system> entity.
trans-unit.target: This topic provides descriptions of the properties of the <system>Contact</system> entity.

trans-unit.source: The <system>Contact</system> entity has the following properties:
trans-unit.target: The <system>Contact</system> entity has the following properties:

trans-unit.source: The city in which the contact is located.
trans-unit.target: The city in which the contact is located.

trans-unit.source: The country/region in which the contact is located.
trans-unit.target: The country/region in which the contact is located.

trans-unit.source: The name for the department in which the contact works.
trans-unit.target: The name for the department in which the contact works.

trans-unit.source: Indicates whether this object was synced from the on-premises directory.
trans-unit.target: Indicates whether this object was synced from the on-premises directory.

trans-unit.source: The display name for the contact.
trans-unit.target: The display name for the contact.

trans-unit.source: The telephone number of the contact’s business fax machine.
trans-unit.target: The telephone number of the contact’s business fax machine.

trans-unit.source: The given name (first name) of the contact.
trans-unit.target: The given name (first name) of the contact.

trans-unit.source: Indicates the last time at which the object was synced with the on-premises directory.
trans-unit.target: Indicates the last time at which the object was synced with the on-premises directory.

trans-unit.source: The SMTP address for the contact, for example, "jeff@contoso.onmicrosoft.com".
trans-unit.target: The SMTP address for the contact, for example, "jeff@contoso.onmicrosoft.com".

trans-unit.source: The mail alias for the contact.
trans-unit.target: The mail alias for the contact.

trans-unit.source: The primary cellular telephone number for the contact.
trans-unit.target: The primary cellular telephone number for the contact.

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier for the contact.
trans-unit.target: The unique identifier for the contact.

trans-unit.source: A string that identifies the object type.
trans-unit.target: A string that identifies the object type.

trans-unit.source: For contacts the value is always “Contact”.
trans-unit.target: For contacts the value is always “Contact”.

trans-unit.source: The office location in the contact's place of business.
trans-unit.target: The office location in the contact's place of business.

trans-unit.source: The postal code for the contact's postal address.
trans-unit.target: The postal code for the contact's postal address.

trans-unit.source: The postal code is specific to the contact's country/region.
trans-unit.target: The postal code is specific to the contact's country/region.

trans-unit.source: In the United States of America, this attribute contains the ZIP code.
trans-unit.target: In the United States of America, this attribute contains the ZIP code.

trans-unit.source: A collection of error details that are preventing this contact from being provisioned successfully.
trans-unit.target: A collection of error details that are preventing this contact from being provisioned successfully.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the voice over IP (VOIP) session initiation protocol (SIP) address for the contact.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the voice over IP (VOIP) session initiation protocol (SIP) address for the contact.

trans-unit.source: The state or province in the contact's address.
trans-unit.target: The state or province in the contact's address.

trans-unit.source: The street address of the contact's place of business.
trans-unit.target: The street address of the contact's place of business.

trans-unit.source: The contact's surname (family name or last name).
trans-unit.target: The contact's surname (family name or last name).

trans-unit.source: The primary telephone number of the contact's place of business.
trans-unit.target: The primary telephone number of the contact's place of business.

trans-unit.source: A thumbnail photo to be displayed for the contact.
trans-unit.target: A thumbnail photo to be displayed for the contact.

trans-unit.target: For information about the primitive types exposed by the EDM, see <externalLink><linkText>Entity Data Model: Primitive Data Types</linkText><linkUri>http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee382832.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>.

trans-unit.source: (Only User and Contact objects are supported.)
trans-unit.target: (Only User and Contact objects are supported.)

trans-unit.source: The user or contact that is this contact’s manager.
trans-unit.target: The user or contact that is this contact’s manager.

trans-unit.source: (Only User and Contact objects are supported.)
trans-unit.target: (Only User and Contact objects are supported.)

trans-unit.source: (The users and contacts that have their manager property set to this contact.)
trans-unit.target: (The users and contacts that have their manager property set to this contact.)

trans-unit.source: Groups that this contact is a member of.
trans-unit.target: Groups that this contact is a member of.

trans-unit.source: <system>Contact</system> also inherits the other navigation properties from <link xlink:href="b0c66543-c74f-4e46-b617-76f9b780e99e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DirectoryObject</link>; however, these properties are not valid for contacts.
trans-unit.target: <system>Contact</system> also inherits the other navigation properties from <link xlink:href="b0c66543-c74f-4e46-b617-76f9b780e99e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">DirectoryObject</link>; however, these properties are not valid for contacts.

trans-unit.source: If a request for any of these properties is sent, a <system>400 Bad Request</system> response is returned.
trans-unit.target: If a request for any of these properties is sent, a <system>400 Bad Request</system> response is returned.

trans-unit.source: The following operations are supported on contacts (the HTTP method used for each is in parentheses):
trans-unit.target: The following operations are supported on contacts (the HTTP method used for each is in parentheses):

trans-unit.source: Update (PATCH): only contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).
trans-unit.target: Update (PATCH): only contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).

trans-unit.source: The following operations are supported on contact navigation properties; not all operations are supported on every navigation property.
trans-unit.target: The following operations are supported on contact navigation properties; not all operations are supported on every navigation property.

trans-unit.source: Update (PUT): <system>manager</system> property, only on contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).
trans-unit.target: Update (PUT): <system>manager</system> property, only on contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).

trans-unit.source: Delete (DELETE): <system>manager</system> property, only on contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).
trans-unit.target: Delete (DELETE): <system>manager</system> property, only on contacts that are not synced from an on-premises directory (<system>dirSyncEnabled</system> is <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>).

trans-unit.source: The principal must be in an administrator role that has permissions to modify contact objects to send PUT or DELETE requests.
trans-unit.target: The principal must be in an administrator role that has permissions to modify contact objects to send PUT or DELETE requests.

trans-unit.source: It must be in a role that has permissions to read contact objects to send GET requests.
trans-unit.target: It must be in a role that has permissions to read contact objects to send GET requests.

trans-unit.source: The following actions and functions may be called on contacts:
trans-unit.target: The following actions and functions may be called on contacts:

trans-unit.source: <link xlink:href="376b9965-8787-4bbd-b0d4-f05bb072ab12" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">checkMemberGroups</link> to check a contact’s membership in a list of groups.
trans-unit.target: <link xlink:href="376b9965-8787-4bbd-b0d4-f05bb072ab12" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">checkMemberGroups</link> to check a contact’s membership in a list of groups.

trans-unit.source: <link xlink:href="64ba0b59-8ae8-4c7b-b3ce-61f417318b59" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">getMemberGroups</link> to return a list of the groups that a contact is a member of.
trans-unit.target: <link xlink:href="64ba0b59-8ae8-4c7b-b3ce-61f417318b59" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">getMemberGroups</link> to return a list of the groups that a contact is a member of.

trans-unit.source: <link xlink:href="eb34602a-15b7-4c73-a632-003fe108184b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">isMemberOf</link> to check whether a contact is a member of a specified group.
trans-unit.target: <link xlink:href="eb34602a-15b7-4c73-a632-003fe108184b" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">isMemberOf</link> to check whether a contact is a member of a specified group.

trans-unit.source: Contacts are mail-enabled entities and cannot be created by using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: Contacts are mail-enabled entities and cannot be created by using Azure AD Graph.

trans-unit.source: They can be updated; however, this is only supported for contacts with the <system>dirSyncEnabled</system> property set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>.
trans-unit.target: They can be updated; however, this is only supported for contacts with the <system>dirSyncEnabled</system> property set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>.
